{"kind":"textbox","id":"sh/kjmdwfqt","slide":6,"name":"text","text":"The bank sees the pattern—and can act on it.","textPreview":"The bank sees the pattern—and can act on it.","textChars":44,"textLines":1,"bbox":[62,570,440,58]}
{"kind":"image","id":"im/fup8zyds","slide":6,"name":"","alt":"Bank fraud operations workspace with one prioritized campaign and next action","bbox":[0,0,1280,720]}
{"kind":"notes","id":"nt/u6pcr8","slide":6,"text":"This gives bank teams a different operating view.\nInstead of investigating 50 disconnected complaints, they can see one active campaign affecting several banks, the evidence connecting those cases, and the next action to take.\nFor example: review two beneficiary accounts, escalate an active phishing domain, or export high-confidence accounts for blocking."}
